  25. ‌type constant =
  26.   | Pconst_integer of string * char option
  27.       (** Integer constants such as [3] [3l] [3L] [3n].

  29.      Suffixes [[g-z][G-Z]] are accepted by the parser.
  30.      Suffixes except ['l'], ['L'] and ['n'] are rejected by the typechecker
  31.   *)
  32.   | Pconst_char of char  (** Character such as ['c']. *)
  33.   | Pconst_string of string * Location.t * string option
  34.       (** Constant string such as ["constant"] or
  35.           [{delim|other constant|delim}].

  37.      The location span the content of the string, without the delimiters.
  38.   *)
  39.   | Pconst_float of string * char option
  40.       (** Float constant such as [3.4], [2e5] or [1.4e-4].

  42.      Suffixes [g-z][G-Z] are accepted by the parser.
  43.      Suffixes are rejected by the typechecker.
  44.   *)

  46. ‌type location_stack = Location.t list

  50. ‌type attribute = {
  51.     attr_name : string loc;
  52.     attr_payload : payload;
  53.     attr_loc : Location.t;
  54.   }
  55. (** Attributes such as [[\@id ARG]] and [[\@\@id ARG]].

  57.           Metadata containers passed around within the AST.
  58.           The compiler ignores unknown attributes.
  59.        *)

  61. ‌and extension = string loc * payload
  62. (** Extension points such as [[%id ARG] and [%%id ARG]].

  64.          Sub-language placeholder -- rejected by the typechecker.
  65.       *)

  67. ‌and attributes = attribute list

  69. ‌and payload =
  70.   | PStr of structure
  71.   | PSig of signature  (** [: SIG] in an attribute or an extension point *)
  72.   | PTyp of core_type  (** [: T] in an attribute or an extension point *)
  73.   | PPat of pattern * expression option
  74.       (** [? P]  or  [? P when E], in an attribute or an extension point *)

  79. ‌and core_type =
  80.     {
  81.      ptyp_desc: core_type_desc;
  82.      ptyp_loc: Location.t;

  87. ‌and core_type_desc =
  88.   | Ptyp_any  (** [_] *)
  89.   | Ptyp_var of string  (** A type variable such as ['a] *)
  90.   | Ptyp_arrow of arg_label * core_type * core_type
  91.       (** [Ptyp_arrow(lbl, T1, T2)] represents:
  92.             - [T1 -> T2]    when [lbl] is
  93.                                      {{!Asttypes.arg_label.Nolabel}[Nolabel]},
  94.             - [~l:T1 -> T2] when [lbl] is
  95.                                      {{!Asttypes.arg_label.Labelled}[Labelled]},
  96.             - [?l:T1 -> T2] when [lbl] is
  97.                                      {{!Asttypes.arg_label.Optional}[Optional]}.
  98.          *)
  99.   | Ptyp_tuple of core_type list
  100.       (** [Ptyp_tuple([T1 ; ... ; Tn])]
  101.           represents a product type [T1 * ... * Tn].

  103.            Invariant: [n >= 2].
  104.         *)
  105.   | Ptyp_constr of Longident.t loc * core_type list
  106.       (** [Ptyp_constr(lident, l)] represents:
  107.             - [tconstr]               when [l=[]],
  108.             - [T tconstr]             when [l=[T]],
  109.             - [(T1, ..., Tn) tconstr] when [l=[T1 ; ... ; Tn]].
  110.          *)
  111.   | Ptyp_object of object_field list * closed_flag
  112.       (** [Ptyp_object([ l1:T1; ...; ln:Tn ], flag)] represents:
  113.             - [< l1:T1; ...; ln:Tn >]     when [flag] is
  114.                                        {{!Asttypes.closed_flag.Closed}[Closed]},
  115.             - [< l1:T1; ...; ln:Tn; .. >] when [flag] is
  116.                                            {{!Asttypes.closed_flag.Open}[Open]}.
  117.          *)
  118.   | Ptyp_class of Longident.t loc * core_type list
  119.       (** [Ptyp_class(tconstr, l)] represents:
  120.             - [#tconstr]               when [l=[]],
  121.             - [T #tconstr]             when [l=[T]],
  122.             - [(T1, ..., Tn) #tconstr] when [l=[T1 ; ... ; Tn]].
  123.          *)
  124.   | Ptyp_alias of core_type * string  (** [T as 'a]. *)
  125.   | Ptyp_variant of row_field list * closed_flag * label list option
  126.       (** [Ptyp_variant([`A;`B], flag, labels)] represents:
  127.             - [[ `A|`B ]]
  128.                       when [flag]   is {{!Asttypes.closed_flag.Closed}[Closed]},
  129.                        and [labels] is [None],
  130.             - [[> `A|`B ]]
  131.                       when [flag]   is {{!Asttypes.closed_flag.Open}[Open]},
  132.                        and [labels] is [None],
  133.             - [[< `A|`B ]]
  134.                       when [flag]   is {{!Asttypes.closed_flag.Closed}[Closed]},
  135.                        and [labels] is [Some []],
  136.             - [[< `A|`B > `X `Y ]]
  137.                       when [flag]   is {{!Asttypes.closed_flag.Closed}[Closed]},
  138.                        and [labels] is [Some ["X";"Y"]].
  139.          *)
  140.   | Ptyp_poly of string loc list * core_type
  141.       (** ['a1 ... 'an. T]

  143.            Can only appear in the following context:

  145.            - As the {!core_type} of a
  146.           {{!pattern_desc.Ppat_constraint}[Ppat_constraint]} node corresponding
  147.              to a constraint on a let-binding:
  148.             {[let x : 'a1 ... 'an. T = e ...]}

  150.            - Under {{!class_field_kind.Cfk_virtual}[Cfk_virtual]} for methods
  151.           (not values).

  153.            - As the {!core_type} of a
  154.            {{!class_type_field_desc.Pctf_method}[Pctf_method]} node.

  156.            - As the {!core_type} of a {{!expression_desc.Pexp_poly}[Pexp_poly]}
  157.            node.

  159.            - As the {{!label_declaration.pld_type}[pld_type]} field of a
  160.            {!label_declaration}.

  162.            - As a {!core_type} of a {{!core_type_desc.Ptyp_object}[Ptyp_object]}
  163.            node.

  165.            - As the {{!value_description.pval_type}[pval_type]} field of a
  166.            {!value_description}.
  167.          *)
  168.   | Ptyp_package of package_type  (** [(module S)]. *)
  169.   | Ptyp_extension of extension  (** [[%id]]. *)

  171. ‌and package_type = Longident.t loc * (Longident.t loc * core_type) list
  172. (** As {!package_type} typed values:
  173.          - [(S, [])] represents [(module S)],
  174.          - [(S, [(t1, T1) ; ... ; (tn, Tn)])]
  175.           represents [(module S with type t1 = T1 and ... and tn = Tn)].
  176.        *)

  178. ‌and row_field = {
  179.   prf_desc : row_field_desc;
  180.   prf_loc : Location.t;
  181.   prf_attributes : attributes;
  182. }

  184. ‌and row_field_desc =
  185.   | Rtag of label loc * bool * core_type list
  186.       (** [Rtag(`A, b, l)] represents:
  187.            - [`A]                   when [b] is [true]  and [l] is [[]],
  188.            - [`A of T]              when [b] is [false] and [l] is [[T]],
  189.            - [`A of T1 & .. & Tn]   when [b] is [false] and [l] is [[T1;...Tn]],
  190.            - [`A of & T1 & .. & Tn] when [b] is [true]  and [l] is [[T1;...Tn]].

  192.           - The [bool] field is true if the tag contains a
  193.             constant (empty) constructor.
  194.           - [&] occurs when several types are used for the same constructor
  195.             (see 4.2 in the manual)
  196.         *)
  197.   | Rinherit of core_type  (** [[ | t ]] *)

  199. ‌and object_field = {

  202.   pof_attributes : attributes;
  203. }

  205. ‌and object_field_desc =
  206.   | Otag of label loc * core_type
  207.   | Oinherit of core_type

  211. ‌and pattern =
  212.     {
  213.      ppat_desc: pattern_desc;
  214.      ppat_loc: Location.t;

  219. ‌and pattern_desc =
  220.   | Ppat_any  (** The pattern [_]. *)
  221.   | Ppat_var of string loc  (** A variable pattern such as [x] *)
  222.   | Ppat_alias of pattern * string loc
  223.       (** An alias pattern such as [P as 'a] *)
  224.   | Ppat_constant of constant
  225.       (** Patterns such as [1], ['a'], ["true"], [1.0], [1l], [1L], [1n] *)
  226.   | Ppat_interval of constant * constant
  227.       (** Patterns such as ['a'..'z'].

  229.            Other forms of interval are recognized by the parser
  230.            but rejected by the type-checker. *)
  231.   | Ppat_tuple of pattern list
  232.       (** Patterns [(P1, ..., Pn)].

  234.            Invariant: [n >= 2]
  235.         *)
  236.   | Ppat_construct of Longident.t loc * (string loc list * pattern) option
  237.       (** [Ppat_construct(C, args)] represents:
  238.             - [C]               when [args] is [None],
  239.             - [C P]             when [args] is [Some ([], P)]
  240.             - [C (P1, ..., Pn)] when [args] is
  241.                                            [Some ([], Ppat_tuple [P1; ...; Pn])]
  242.             - [C (type a b) P]  when [args] is [Some ([a; b], P)]
  243.          *)
  244.   | Ppat_variant of label * pattern option
  245.       (** [Ppat_variant(`A, pat)] represents:
  246.             - [`A]   when [pat] is [None],
  247.             - [`A P] when [pat] is [Some P]
  248.          *)
  249.   | Ppat_record of (Longident.t loc * pattern) list * closed_flag
  250.       (** [Ppat_record([(l1, P1) ; ... ; (ln, Pn)], flag)] represents:
  251.             - [{ l1=P1; ...; ln=Pn }]
  252.                  when [flag] is {{!Asttypes.closed_flag.Closed}[Closed]}
  253.             - [{ l1=P1; ...; ln=Pn; _}]
  254.                  when [flag] is {{!Asttypes.closed_flag.Open}[Open]}

  256.            Invariant: [n > 0]
  257.          *)
  258.   | Ppat_array of pattern list  (** Pattern [[| P1; ...; Pn |]] *)
  259.   | Ppat_or of pattern * pattern  (** Pattern [P1 | P2] *)
  260.   | Ppat_constraint of pattern * core_type  (** Pattern [(P : T)] *)
  261.   | Ppat_type of Longident.t loc  (** Pattern [#tconst] *)
  262.   | Ppat_lazy of pattern  (** Pattern [lazy P] *)
  263.   | Ppat_unpack of string option loc
  264.       (** [Ppat_unpack(s)] represents:
  265.             - [(module P)] when [s] is [Some "P"]
  266.             - [(module _)] when [s] is [None]

  268.            Note: [(module P : S)] is represented as
  269.            [Ppat_constraint(Ppat_unpack(Some "P"), Ptyp_package S)]
  270.          *)
  271.   | Ppat_exception of pattern  (** Pattern [exception P] *)
  272.   | Ppat_extension of extension  (** Pattern [[%id]] *)
  273.   | Ppat_open of Longident.t loc * pattern  (** Pattern [M.(P)] *)

  277. ‌and expression =
  278.     {
  279.      pexp_desc: expression_desc;
  280.      pexp_loc: Location.t;
  281.      pexp_loc_stack: location_stack;
  282.      pexp_attributes: attributes;  (** [... [\@id1] [\@id2]] *)

  285. ‌and expression_desc =
  286.   | Pexp_ident of Longident.t loc
  287.       (** Identifiers such as [x] and [M.x]
  288.          *)
  289.   | Pexp_constant of constant
  290.       (** Expressions constant such as [1], ['a'], ["true"], [1.0], [1l],
  291.             [1L], [1n] *)
  292.   | Pexp_let of rec_flag * value_binding list * expression
  293.       (** [Pexp_let(flag, [(P1,E1) ; ... ; (Pn,En)], E)] represents:
  294.             - [let P1 = E1 and ... and Pn = EN in E]
  295.                when [flag] is {{!Asttypes.rec_flag.Nonrecursive}[Nonrecursive]},
  296.             - [let rec P1 = E1 and ... and Pn = EN in E]
  297.                when [flag] is {{!Asttypes.rec_flag.Recursive}[Recursive]}.
  298.          *)
  299.   | Pexp_function of case list  (** [function P1 -> E1 | ... | Pn -> En] *)
  300.   | Pexp_fun of arg_label * expression option * pattern * expression
  301.       (** [Pexp_fun(lbl, exp0, P, E1)] represents:
  302.             - [fun P -> E1]
  303.                       when [lbl] is {{!Asttypes.arg_label.Nolabel}[Nolabel]}
  304.                        and [exp0] is [None]
  305.             - [fun ~l:P -> E1]
  306.                       when [lbl] is {{!Asttypes.arg_label.Labelled}[Labelled l]}
  307.                        and [exp0] is [None]
  308.             - [fun ?l:P -> E1]
  309.                       when [lbl] is {{!Asttypes.arg_label.Optional}[Optional l]}
  310.                        and [exp0] is [None]
  311.             - [fun ?l:(P = E0) -> E1]
  312.                       when [lbl] is {{!Asttypes.arg_label.Optional}[Optional l]}
  313.                        and [exp0] is [Some E0]

  315.            Notes:
  316.            - If [E0] is provided, only
  317.              {{!Asttypes.arg_label.Optional}[Optional]} is allowed.
  318.            - [fun P1 P2 .. Pn -> E1] is represented as nested
  319.              {{!expression_desc.Pexp_fun}[Pexp_fun]}.
  320.            - [let f P = E] is represented using
  321.              {{!expression_desc.Pexp_fun}[Pexp_fun]}.
  322.          *)
  323.   | Pexp_apply of expression * (arg_label * expression) list
  324.       (** [Pexp_apply(E0, [(l1, E1) ; ... ; (ln, En)])]
  325.             represents [E0 ~l1:E1 ... ~ln:En]

  327.             [li] can be
  328.               {{!Asttypes.arg_label.Nolabel}[Nolabel]}   (non labeled argument),
  329.               {{!Asttypes.arg_label.Labelled}[Labelled]} (labelled arguments) or
  330.               {{!Asttypes.arg_label.Optional}[Optional]} (optional argument).

  332.            Invariant: [n > 0]
  333.          *)
  334.   | Pexp_match of expression * case list
  335.       (** [match E0 with P1 -> E1 | ... | Pn -> En] *)
  336.   | Pexp_try of expression * case list
  337.       (** [try E0 with P1 -> E1 | ... | Pn -> En] *)
  338.   | Pexp_tuple of expression list
  339.       (** Expressions [(E1, ..., En)]

  341.            Invariant: [n >= 2]
  342.         *)
  343.   | Pexp_construct of Longident.t loc * expression option
  344.       (** [Pexp_construct(C, exp)] represents:
  345.            - [C]               when [exp] is [None],
  346.            - [C E]             when [exp] is [Some E],
  347.            - [C (E1, ..., En)] when [exp] is [Some (Pexp_tuple[E1;...;En])]
  348.         *)
  349.   | Pexp_variant of label * expression option
  350.       (** [Pexp_variant(`A, exp)] represents
  351.             - [`A]   when [exp] is [None]
  352.             - [`A E] when [exp] is [Some E]
  353.          *)
  354.   | Pexp_record of (Longident.t loc * expression) list * expression option
  355.       (** [Pexp_record([(l1,P1) ; ... ; (ln,Pn)], exp0)] represents
  356.             - [{ l1=P1; ...; ln=Pn }]         when [exp0] is [None]
  357.             - [{ E0 with l1=P1; ...; ln=Pn }] when [exp0] is [Some E0]

  359.            Invariant: [n > 0]
  360.          *)
  361.   | Pexp_field of expression * Longident.t loc  (** [E.l] *)
  362.   | Pexp_setfield of expression * Longident.t loc * expression
  363.       (** [E1.l <- E2] *)
  364.   | Pexp_array of expression list  (** [[| E1; ...; En |]] *)
  365.   | Pexp_ifthenelse of expression * expression * expression option
  366.       (** [if E1 then E2 else E3] *)
  367.   | Pexp_sequence of expression * expression  (** [E1; E2] *)
  368.   | Pexp_while of expression * expression  (** [while E1 do E2 done] *)
  369.   | Pexp_for of pattern * expression * expression * direction_flag * expression
  370.       (** [Pexp_for(i, E1, E2, direction, E3)] represents:
  371.             - [for i = E1 to E2 do E3 done]
  372.                  when [direction] is {{!Asttypes.direction_flag.Upto}[Upto]}
  373.             - [for i = E1 downto E2 do E3 done]
  374.                  when [direction] is {{!Asttypes.direction_flag.Downto}[Downto]}
  375.          *)
  376.   | Pexp_constraint of expression * core_type  (** [(E : T)] *)
  377.   | Pexp_coerce of expression * core_type option * core_type
  378.       (** [Pexp_coerce(E, from, T)] represents
  379.             - [(E :> T)]      when [from] is [None],
  380.             - [(E : T0 :> T)] when [from] is [Some T0].
  381.          *)
  382.   | Pexp_send of expression * label loc  (** [E # m] *)
  383.   | Pexp_new of Longident.t loc  (** [new M.c] *)
  384.   | Pexp_setinstvar of label loc * expression  (** [x <- 2] *)
  385.   | Pexp_override of (label loc * expression) list
  386.       (** [{< x1 = E1; ...; xn = En >}] *)
  387.   | Pexp_letmodule of string option loc * module_expr * expression
  388.       (** [let module M = ME in E] *)
  389.   | Pexp_letexception of extension_constructor * expression
  390.       (** [let exception C in E] *)
  391.   | Pexp_assert of expression
  392.       (** [assert E].

  394.            Note: [assert false] is treated in a special way by the
  395.            type-checker. *)
  396.   | Pexp_lazy of expression  (** [lazy E] *)
  397.   | Pexp_poly of expression * core_type option
  398.       (** Used for method bodies.

  400.            Can only be used as the expression under
  401.            {{!class_field_kind.Cfk_concrete}[Cfk_concrete]} for methods (not
  402.            values). *)
  403.   | Pexp_object of class_structure  (** [object ... end] *)
  404.   | Pexp_newtype of string loc * expression  (** [fun (type t) -> E] *)
  405.   | Pexp_pack of module_expr
  406.       (** [(module ME)].

  408.            [(module ME : S)] is represented as
  409.            [Pexp_constraint(Pexp_pack ME, Ptyp_package S)] *)
  410.   | Pexp_open of open_declaration * expression
  411.       (** - [M.(E)]
  412.             - [let open M in E]
  413.             - [let open! M in E] *)
  414.   | Pexp_letop of letop
  415.       (** - [let* P = E0 in E1]
  416.             - [let* P0 = E00 and* P1 = E01 in E1] *)
  417.   | Pexp_extension of extension  (** [[%id]] *)
  418.   | Pexp_unreachable  (** [.] *)

  420. ‌and case =
  421.     {
  422.      pc_lhs: pattern;
  423.      pc_guard: expression option;
  424.      pc_rhs: expression;
  425.    }
  426. (** Values of type {!case} represents [(P -> E)] or [(P when E0 -> E)] *)

  428. ‌and letop =
  429.   {
  430.     let_ : binding_op;
  431.     ands : binding_op list;
  432.     body : expression;
  433.   }

  435. ‌and binding_op =
  436.   {
  437.     pbop_op : string loc;
  438.     pbop_pat : pattern;
  439.     pbop_exp : expression;
  440.     pbop_loc : Location.t;
  441.   }

  443. (** {2 Value descriptions} *)

  445. ‌and value_description =
  446.     {
  447.      pval_name: string loc;
  448.      pval_type: core_type;
  449.      pval_prim: string list;
  450.      pval_attributes: attributes;  (** [... [\@\@id1] [\@\@id2]] *)
  451.      pval_loc: Location.t;
  452.     }
  453. (** Values of type {!value_description} represents:
  454.     - [val x: T],
  455.             when {{!value_description.pval_prim}[pval_prim]} is [[]]
  456.     - [external x: T = "s1" ... "sn"]
  457.             when {{!value_description.pval_prim}[pval_prim]} is [["s1";..."sn"]]
  458. *)

  460. (** {2 Type declarations} *)

  462. ‌and type_declaration =
  463.     {
  464.      ptype_name: string loc;
  465.      ptype_params: (core_type * (variance * injectivity)) list;
  466.       (** [('a1,...'an) t] *)
  467.      ptype_cstrs: (core_type * core_type * Location.t) list;
  468.       (** [... constraint T1=T1'  ... constraint Tn=Tn'] *)
  469.      ptype_kind: type_kind;
  470.      ptype_private: private_flag;  (** for [= private ...] *)
  471.      ptype_manifest: core_type option;  (** represents [= T] *)
  472.      ptype_attributes: attributes;  (** [... [\@\@id1] [\@\@id2]] *)
  473.      ptype_loc: Location.t;
  474.     }
  475. (**
  476.    Here are type declarations and their representation,
  477.    for various {{!type_declaration.ptype_kind}[ptype_kind]}
  478.            and {{!type_declaration.ptype_manifest}[ptype_manifest]} values:
  479. - [type t]   when [type_kind] is {{!type_kind.Ptype_abstract}[Ptype_abstract]},
  480.                and [manifest]  is [None],
  481. - [type t = T0]
  482.               when [type_kind] is {{!type_kind.Ptype_abstract}[Ptype_abstract]},
  483.                and [manifest]  is [Some T0],
  484. - [type t = C of T | ...]
  485.               when [type_kind] is {{!type_kind.Ptype_variant}[Ptype_variant]},
  486.                and [manifest]  is [None],
  487. - [type t = T0 = C of T | ...]
  488.               when [type_kind] is {{!type_kind.Ptype_variant}[Ptype_variant]},
  489.                and [manifest]  is [Some T0],
  490. - [type t = {l: T; ...}]
  491.               when [type_kind] is {{!type_kind.Ptype_record}[Ptype_record]},
  492.                and [manifest]  is [None],
  493. - [type t = T0 = {l : T; ...}]
  494.               when [type_kind] is {{!type_kind.Ptype_record}[Ptype_record]},
  495.                and [manifest]  is [Some T0],
  496. - [type t = ..]
  497.               when [type_kind] is {{!type_kind.Ptype_open}[Ptype_open]},
  498.                and [manifest]  is [None].
  499. *)

  501. ‌and type_kind =
  502.   | Ptype_abstract
  503.   | Ptype_variant of constructor_declaration list
  504.   | Ptype_record of label_declaration list  (** Invariant: non-empty list *)
  505.   | Ptype_open

  507. ‌and label_declaration =
  508.     {
  509.      pld_name: string loc;
  510.      pld_mutable: mutable_flag;
  511.      pld_type: core_type;
  512.      pld_loc: Location.t;
  513.      pld_attributes: attributes;  (** [l : T [\@id1] [\@id2]] *)
  514.     }
  515. (**
  516.    - [{ ...; l: T; ... }]
  517.                            when {{!label_declaration.pld_mutable}[pld_mutable]}
  518.                              is {{!Asttypes.mutable_flag.Immutable}[Immutable]},
  519.    - [{ ...; mutable l: T; ... }]
  520.                            when {{!label_declaration.pld_mutable}[pld_mutable]}
  521.                              is {{!Asttypes.mutable_flag.Mutable}[Mutable]}.

  523.    Note: [T] can be a {{!core_type_desc.Ptyp_poly}[Ptyp_poly]}.
  524. *)

  526. ‌and constructor_declaration =
  527.     {
  528.      pcd_name: string loc;
  529.      pcd_vars: string loc list;
  530.      pcd_args: constructor_arguments;
  531.      pcd_res: core_type option;
  532.      pcd_loc: Location.t;
  533.      pcd_attributes: attributes;  (** [C of ... [\@id1] [\@id2]] *)
  534.     }

  536. ‌and constructor_arguments =
  537.   | Pcstr_tuple of core_type list
  538.   | Pcstr_record of label_declaration list
  539.       (** Values of type {!constructor_declaration}
  540.     represents the constructor arguments of:
  541.   - [C of T1 * ... * Tn]     when [res = None],
  542.                               and [args = Pcstr_tuple [T1; ... ; Tn]],
  543.   - [C: T0]                  when [res = Some T0],
  544.                               and [args = Pcstr_tuple []],
  545.   - [C: T1 * ... * Tn -> T0] when [res = Some T0],
  546.                               and [args = Pcstr_tuple [T1; ... ; Tn]],
  547.   - [C of {...}]             when [res = None],
  548.                               and [args = Pcstr_record [...]],
  549.   - [C: {...} -> T0]         when [res = Some T0],
  550.                               and [args = Pcstr_record [...]].
  551. *)

  553. ‌and type_extension =
  554.     {
  555.      ptyext_path: Longident.t loc;
  556.      ptyext_params: (core_type * (variance * injectivity)) list;
  557.      ptyext_constructors: extension_constructor list;
  558.      ptyext_private: private_flag;
  559.      ptyext_loc: Location.t;
  560.      ptyext_attributes: attributes;  (** ... [\@\@id1] [\@\@id2] *)
  561.     }
  562. (**
  563.    Definition of new extensions constructors for the extensive sum type [t]
  564.    ([type t += ...]).
  565. *)

  567. ‌and extension_constructor =
  568.     {
  569.      pext_name: string loc;
  570.      pext_kind: extension_constructor_kind;
  571.      pext_loc: Location.t;
  572.      pext_attributes: attributes;  (** [C of ... [\@id1] [\@id2]] *)
  573.    }

  575. ‌and type_exception =
  576.   {
  577.     ptyexn_constructor : extension_constructor;
  578.     ptyexn_loc : Location.t;
  579.     ptyexn_attributes : attributes;  (** [... [\@\@id1] [\@\@id2]] *)
  580.   }
  581. (** Definition of a new exception ([exception E]). *)

  583. ‌and extension_constructor_kind =
  584.   | Pext_decl of string loc list * constructor_arguments * core_type option
  585.       (** [Pext_decl(existentials, c_args, t_opt)]
  586.           describes a new extension constructor. It can be:
  587.           - [C of T1 * ... * Tn] when:
  588.                {ul {- [existentials] is [[]],}
  589.                    {- [c_args] is [[T1; ...; Tn]],}
  590.                    {- [t_opt] is [None]}.}
  591.           - [C: T0] when
  592.                {ul {- [existentials] is [[]],}
  593.                    {- [c_args] is [[]],}
  594.                    {- [t_opt] is [Some T0].}}
  595.           - [C: T1 * ... * Tn -> T0] when
  596.                {ul {- [existentials] is [[]],}
  597.                    {- [c_args] is [[T1; ...; Tn]],}
  598.                    {- [t_opt] is [Some T0].}}
  599.           - [C: 'a... . T1 * ... * Tn -> T0] when
  600.                {ul {- [existentials] is [['a;...]],}
  601.                    {- [c_args] is [[T1; ... ; Tn]],}
  602.                    {- [t_opt] is [Some T0].}}
  603.        *)
  604.   | Pext_rebind of Longident.t loc
  605.   (** [Pext_rebind(D)] re-export the constructor [D] with the new name [C] *)

  607. (** {1 Class language} *)
  608. (** {2 Type expressions for the class language} *)

  610. ‌and class_type =
  611.     {
  612.      pcty_desc: class_type_desc;
  613.      pcty_loc: Location.t;
  614.      pcty_attributes: attributes;  (** [... [\@id1] [\@id2]] *)
  615.     }

  617. ‌and class_type_desc =
  618.   | Pcty_constr of Longident.t loc * core_type list
  619.       (** - [c]
  620.             - [['a1, ..., 'an] c] *)
  621.   | Pcty_signature of class_signature  (** [object ... end] *)
  622.   | Pcty_arrow of arg_label * core_type * class_type
  623.       (** [Pcty_arrow(lbl, T, CT)] represents:
  624.             - [T -> CT]
  625.                      when [lbl] is {{!Asttypes.arg_label.Nolabel}[Nolabel]},
  626.             - [~l:T -> CT]
  627.                      when [lbl] is {{!Asttypes.arg_label.Labelled}[Labelled l]},
  628.             - [?l:T -> CT]
  629.                      when [lbl] is {{!Asttypes.arg_label.Optional}[Optional l]}.
  630.          *)
  631.   | Pcty_extension of extension  (** [%id] *)
  632.   | Pcty_open of open_description * class_type  (** [let open M in CT] *)

  634. ‌and class_signature =
  635.     {
  636.      pcsig_self: core_type;
  637.      pcsig_fields: class_type_field list;
  638.     }
  639. (** Values of type [class_signature] represents:
  640.     - [object('selfpat) ... end]
  641.     - [object ... end] when {{!class_signature.pcsig_self}[pcsig_self]}
  642.                          is {{!core_type_desc.Ptyp_any}[Ptyp_any]}
  643. *)

  645. ‌and class_type_field =
  646.     {
  647.      pctf_desc: class_type_field_desc;
  648.      pctf_loc: Location.t;
  649.      pctf_attributes: attributes;  (** [... [\@\@id1] [\@\@id2]] *)
  650.     }

  652. ‌and class_type_field_desc =
  653.   | Pctf_inherit of class_type  (** [inherit CT] *)
  654.   | Pctf_val of (label loc * mutable_flag * virtual_flag * core_type)
  655.       (** [val x: T] *)
  656.   | Pctf_method of (label loc * private_flag * virtual_flag * core_type)
  657.       (** [method x: T]

  659.             Note: [T] can be a {{!core_type_desc.Ptyp_poly}[Ptyp_poly]}.
  660.         *)
  661.   | Pctf_constraint of (core_type * core_type)  (** [constraint T1 = T2] *)
  662.   | Pctf_attribute of attribute  (** [[\@\@\@id]] *)
  663.   | Pctf_extension of extension  (** [[%%id]] *)

  665. ‌and 'a class_infos =
  666.     {
  667.      pci_virt: virtual_flag;
  668.      pci_params: (core_type * (variance * injectivity)) list;
  669.      pci_name: string loc;
  670.      pci_expr: 'a;
  671.      pci_loc: Location.t;
  672.      pci_attributes: attributes;  (** [... [\@\@id1] [\@\@id2]] *)
  673.     }
  674. (** Values of type [class_expr class_infos] represents:
  675.     - [class c = ...]
  676.     - [class ['a1,...,'an] c = ...]
  677.     - [class virtual c = ...]

  679.    They are also used for "class type" declaration.
  680. *)

  682. ‌and class_description = class_type class_infos

  684. ‌and class_type_declaration = class_type class_infos

  686. (** {2 Value expressions for the class language} *)

  688. ‌and class_expr =
  689.     {
  690.      pcl_desc: class_expr_desc;
  691.      pcl_loc: Location.t;
  692.      pcl_attributes: attributes;  (** [... [\@id1] [\@id2]] *)
  693.     }

  695. ‌and class_expr_desc =
  696.   | Pcl_constr of Longident.t loc * core_type list
  697.       (** [c] and [['a1, ..., 'an] c] *)
  698.   | Pcl_structure of class_structure  (** [object ... end] *)
  699.   | Pcl_fun of arg_label * expression option * pattern * class_expr
  700.       (** [Pcl_fun(lbl, exp0, P, CE)] represents:
  701.             - [fun P -> CE]
  702.                      when [lbl]  is {{!Asttypes.arg_label.Nolabel}[Nolabel]}
  703.                       and [exp0] is [None],
  704.             - [fun ~l:P -> CE]
  705.                      when [lbl]  is {{!Asttypes.arg_label.Labelled}[Labelled l]}
  706.                       and [exp0] is [None],
  707.             - [fun ?l:P -> CE]
  708.                      when [lbl]  is {{!Asttypes.arg_label.Optional}[Optional l]}
  709.                       and [exp0] is [None],
  710.             - [fun ?l:(P = E0) -> CE]
  711.                      when [lbl]  is {{!Asttypes.arg_label.Optional}[Optional l]}
  712.                       and [exp0] is [Some E0].
  713.         *)
  714.   | Pcl_apply of class_expr * (arg_label * expression) list
  715.       (** [Pcl_apply(CE, [(l1,E1) ; ... ; (ln,En)])]
  716.             represents [CE ~l1:E1 ... ~ln:En].
  717.             [li] can be empty (non labeled argument) or start with [?]
  718.             (optional argument).

  720.             Invariant: [n > 0]
  721.         *)
  722.   | Pcl_let of rec_flag * value_binding list * class_expr
  723.       (** [Pcl_let(rec, [(P1, E1); ... ; (Pn, En)], CE)] represents:
  724.             - [let P1 = E1 and ... and Pn = EN in CE]
  725.                 when [rec] is {{!Asttypes.rec_flag.Nonrecursive}[Nonrecursive]},
  726.             - [let rec P1 = E1 and ... and Pn = EN in CE]
  727.                 when [rec] is {{!Asttypes.rec_flag.Recursive}[Recursive]}.
  728.         *)
  729.   | Pcl_constraint of class_expr * class_type  (** [(CE : CT)] *)
  730.   | Pcl_extension of extension  (** [[%id]] *)
  731.   | Pcl_open of open_description * class_expr  (** [let open M in CE] *)

  733. ‌and class_structure =
  734.     {
  735.      pcstr_self: pattern;
  736.      pcstr_fields: class_field list;
  737.     }
  738. (** Values of type {!class_structure} represents:
  739.     - [object(selfpat) ... end]
  740.     - [object ... end] when {{!class_structure.pcstr_self}[pcstr_self]}
  741.                          is {{!pattern_desc.Ppat_any}[Ppat_any]}
  742. *)

  744. ‌and class_field =
  745.     {
  746.      pcf_desc: class_field_desc;
  747.      pcf_loc: Location.t;
  748.      pcf_attributes: attributes;  (** [... [\@\@id1] [\@\@id2]] *)
  749.     }

  751. ‌and class_field_desc =
  752.   | Pcf_inherit of override_flag * class_expr * string loc option
  753.       (** [Pcf_inherit(flag, CE, s)] represents:
  754.             - [inherit CE]
  755.                     when [flag] is {{!Asttypes.override_flag.Fresh}[Fresh]}
  756.                      and [s] is [None],
  757.             - [inherit CE as x]
  758.                    when [flag] is {{!Asttypes.override_flag.Fresh}[Fresh]}
  759.                     and [s] is [Some x],
  760.             - [inherit! CE]
  761.                    when [flag] is {{!Asttypes.override_flag.Override}[Override]}
  762.                     and [s] is [None],
  763.             - [inherit! CE as x]
  764.                    when [flag] is {{!Asttypes.override_flag.Override}[Override]}
  765.                     and [s] is [Some x]
  766.   *)
  767.   | Pcf_val of (label loc * mutable_flag * class_field_kind)
  768.       (** [Pcf_val(x,flag, kind)] represents:
  769.             - [val x = E]
  770.        when [flag] is {{!Asttypes.mutable_flag.Immutable}[Immutable]}
  771.         and [kind] is {{!class_field_kind.Cfk_concrete}[Cfk_concrete(Fresh, E)]}
  772.             - [val virtual x: T]
  773.        when [flag] is {{!Asttypes.mutable_flag.Immutable}[Immutable]}
  774.         and [kind] is {{!class_field_kind.Cfk_virtual}[Cfk_virtual(T)]}
  775.             - [val mutable x = E]
  776.        when [flag] is {{!Asttypes.mutable_flag.Mutable}[Mutable]}
  777.         and [kind] is {{!class_field_kind.Cfk_concrete}[Cfk_concrete(Fresh, E)]}
  778.             - [val mutable virtual x: T]
  779.        when [flag] is {{!Asttypes.mutable_flag.Mutable}[Mutable]}
  780.         and [kind] is {{!class_field_kind.Cfk_virtual}[Cfk_virtual(T)]}
  781.   *)
  782.   | Pcf_method of (label loc * private_flag * class_field_kind)
  783.       (** - [method x = E]
  784.                         ([E] can be a {{!expression_desc.Pexp_poly}[Pexp_poly]})
  785.             - [method virtual x: T]
  786.                         ([T] can be a {{!core_type_desc.Ptyp_poly}[Ptyp_poly]})
  787.   *)
  788.   | Pcf_constraint of (core_type * core_type)  (** [constraint T1 = T2] *)
  789.   | Pcf_initializer of expression  (** [initializer E] *)
  790.   | Pcf_attribute of attribute  (** [[\@\@\@id]] *)
  791.   | Pcf_extension of extension  (** [[%%id]] *)

  793. ‌and class_field_kind =
  794.   | Cfk_virtual of core_type
  795.   | Cfk_concrete of override_flag * expression

  797. ‌and class_declaration = class_expr class_infos

  799. (** {1 Module language} *)
  800. (** {2 Type expressions for the module language} *)

  802. ‌and module_type =
  803.     {
  804.      pmty_desc: module_type_desc;
  805.      pmty_loc: Location.t;
  806.      pmty_attributes: attributes;  (** [... [\@id1] [\@id2]] *)
  807.     }

  809. ‌and module_type_desc =
  810.   | Pmty_ident of Longident.t loc  (** [Pmty_ident(S)] represents [S] *)
  811.   | Pmty_signature of signature  (** [sig ... end] *)
  812.   | Pmty_functor of functor_parameter * module_type
  813.       (** [functor(X : MT1) -> MT2] *)
  814.   | Pmty_with of module_type * with_constraint list  (** [MT with ...] *)
  815.   | Pmty_typeof of module_expr  (** [module type of ME] *)
  816.   | Pmty_extension of extension  (** [[%id]] *)
  817.   | Pmty_alias of Longident.t loc  (** [(module M)] *)

  819. ‌and functor_parameter =
  820.   | Unit  (** [()] *)
  821.   | Named of string option loc * module_type
  822.       (** [Named(name, MT)] represents:
  823.             - [(X : MT)] when [name] is [Some X],
  824.             - [(_ : MT)] when [name] is [None] *)

  826. ‌and signature = signature_item list

  828. ‌and signature_item =
  829.     {
  830.      psig_desc: signature_item_desc;
  831.      psig_loc: Location.t;
  832.     }

  834. ‌and signature_item_desc =
  835.   | Psig_value of value_description
  836.       (** - [val x: T]
  837.             - [external x: T = "s1" ... "sn"]
  838.          *)
  839.   | Psig_type of rec_flag * type_declaration list
  840.       (** [type t1 = ... and ... and tn  = ...] *)
  841.   | Psig_typesubst of type_declaration list
  842.       (** [type t1 := ... and ... and tn := ...]  *)
  843.   | Psig_typext of type_extension  (** [type t1 += ...] *)
  844.   | Psig_exception of type_exception  (** [exception C of T] *)
  845.   | Psig_module of module_declaration  (** [module X = M] and [module X : MT] *)
  846.   | Psig_modsubst of module_substitution  (** [module X := M] *)
  847.   | Psig_recmodule of module_declaration list
  848.       (** [module rec X1 : MT1 and ... and Xn : MTn] *)
  849.   | Psig_modtype of module_type_declaration
  850.       (** [module type S = MT] and [module type S] *)
  851.   | Psig_modtypesubst of module_type_declaration
  852.       (** [module type S :=  ...]  *)
  853.   | Psig_open of open_description  (** [open X] *)
  854.   | Psig_include of include_description  (** [include MT] *)
  855.   | Psig_class of class_description list
  856.       (** [class c1 : ... and ... and cn : ...] *)
  857.   | Psig_class_type of class_type_declaration list
  858.       (** [class type ct1 = ... and ... and ctn = ...] *)
  859.   | Psig_attribute of attribute  (** [[\@\@\@id]] *)
  860.   | Psig_extension of extension * attributes  (** [[%%id]] *)

  862. ‌and module_declaration =
  863.     {
  864.      pmd_name: string option loc;
  865.      pmd_type: module_type;
  866.      pmd_attributes: attributes;  (** [... [\@\@id1] [\@\@id2]] *)
  867.      pmd_loc: Location.t;
  868.     }
  869. (** Values of type [module_declaration] represents [S : MT] *)

  871. ‌and module_substitution =
  872.     {
  873.      pms_name: string loc;
  874.      pms_manifest: Longident.t loc;
  875.      pms_attributes: attributes;  (** [... [\@\@id1] [\@\@id2]] *)
  876.      pms_loc: Location.t;
  877.     }
  878. (** Values of type [module_substitution] represents [S := M] *)

  880. ‌and module_type_declaration =
  881.     {
  882.      pmtd_name: string loc;
  883.      pmtd_type: module_type option;
  884.      pmtd_attributes: attributes;  (** [... [\@\@id1] [\@\@id2]] *)
  885.      pmtd_loc: Location.t;
  886.     }
  887. (** Values of type [module_type_declaration] represents:
  888.    - [S = MT],
  889.    - [S] for abstract module type declaration,
  890.      when {{!module_type_declaration.pmtd_type}[pmtd_type]} is [None].
  891. *)

  893. ‌and 'a open_infos =
  894.     {
  895.      popen_expr: 'a;
  896.      popen_override: override_flag;
  897.      popen_loc: Location.t;
  898.      popen_attributes: attributes;
  899.     }
  900. (** Values of type ['a open_infos] represents:
  901.     - [open! X] when {{!open_infos.popen_override}[popen_override]}
  902.                   is {{!Asttypes.override_flag.Override}[Override]}
  903.     (silences the "used identifier shadowing" warning)
  904.     - [open  X] when {{!open_infos.popen_override}[popen_override]}
  905.                   is {{!Asttypes.override_flag.Fresh}[Fresh]}
  906. *)

  908. ‌and open_description = Longident.t loc open_infos
  909. (** Values of type [open_description] represents:
  910.     - [open M.N]
  911.     - [open M(N).O] *)

  913. ‌and open_declaration = module_expr open_infos
  914. (** Values of type [open_declaration] represents:
  915.     - [open M.N]
  916.     - [open M(N).O]
  917.     - [open struct ... end] *)

  919. ‌and 'a include_infos =
  920.     {
  921.      pincl_mod: 'a;
  922.      pincl_loc: Location.t;
  923.      pincl_attributes: attributes;
  924.     }

  926. ‌and include_description = module_type include_infos
  927. (** Values of type [include_description] represents [include MT] *)

  929. ‌and include_declaration = module_expr include_infos
  930. (** Values of type [include_declaration] represents [include ME] *)

  932. ‌and with_constraint =
  933.   | Pwith_type of Longident.t loc * type_declaration
  934.       (** [with type X.t = ...]

  936.             Note: the last component of the longident must match
  937.             the name of the type_declaration. *)
  938.   | Pwith_module of Longident.t loc * Longident.t loc
  939.       (** [with module X.Y = Z] *)
  940.   | Pwith_modtype of Longident.t loc * module_type
  941.       (** [with module type X.Y = Z] *)
  942.   | Pwith_modtypesubst of Longident.t loc * module_type
  943.       (** [with module type X.Y := sig end] *)
  944.   | Pwith_typesubst of Longident.t loc * type_declaration
  945.       (** [with type X.t := ..., same format as [Pwith_type]] *)
  946.   | Pwith_modsubst of Longident.t loc * Longident.t loc
  947.       (** [with module X.Y := Z] *)

  949. (** {2 Value expressions for the module language} *)

  951. ‌and module_expr =
  952.     {
  953.      pmod_desc: module_expr_desc;
  954.      pmod_loc: Location.t;
  955.      pmod_attributes: attributes;  (** [... [\@id1] [\@id2]] *)
  956.     }

  958. ‌and module_expr_desc =
  959.   | Pmod_ident of Longident.t loc  (** [X] *)
  960.   | Pmod_structure of structure  (** [struct ... end] *)
  961.   | Pmod_functor of functor_parameter * module_expr
  962.       (** [functor(X : MT1) -> ME] *)
  963.   | Pmod_apply of module_expr * module_expr (** [ME1(ME2)] *)
  964.   | Pmod_apply_unit of module_expr (** [ME1()] *)
  965.   | Pmod_constraint of module_expr * module_type  (** [(ME : MT)] *)
  966.   | Pmod_unpack of expression  (** [(val E)] *)
  967.   | Pmod_extension of extension  (** [[%id]] *)

  969. ‌and structure = structure_item list

  971. ‌and structure_item =
  972.     {
  973.      pstr_desc: structure_item_desc;
  974.      pstr_loc: Location.t;
  975.     }

  977. ‌and structure_item_desc =
  978.   | Pstr_eval of expression * attributes  (** [E] *)
  979.   | Pstr_value of rec_flag * value_binding list
  980.       (** [Pstr_value(rec, [(P1, E1 ; ... ; (Pn, En))])] represents:
  981.             - [let P1 = E1 and ... and Pn = EN]
  982.                 when [rec] is {{!Asttypes.rec_flag.Nonrecursive}[Nonrecursive]},
  983.             - [let rec P1 = E1 and ... and Pn = EN ]
  984.                 when [rec] is {{!Asttypes.rec_flag.Recursive}[Recursive]}.
  985.         *)
  986.   | Pstr_primitive of value_description
  987.       (** - [val x: T]
  988.             - [external x: T = "s1" ... "sn" ]*)
  989.   | Pstr_type of rec_flag * type_declaration list
  990.       (** [type t1 = ... and ... and tn = ...] *)
  991.   | Pstr_typext of type_extension  (** [type t1 += ...] *)
  992.   | Pstr_exception of type_exception
  993.       (** - [exception C of T]
  994.             - [exception C = M.X] *)
  995.   | Pstr_module of module_binding  (** [module X = ME] *)
  996.   | Pstr_recmodule of module_binding list
  997.       (** [module rec X1 = ME1 and ... and Xn = MEn] *)
  998.   | Pstr_modtype of module_type_declaration  (** [module type S = MT] *)
  999.   | Pstr_open of open_declaration  (** [open X] *)
  1000.   | Pstr_class of class_declaration list
  1001.       (** [class c1 = ... and ... and cn = ...] *)
  1002.   | Pstr_class_type of class_type_declaration list
  1003.       (** [class type ct1 = ... and ... and ctn = ...] *)
  1004.   | Pstr_include of include_declaration  (** [include ME] *)
  1005.   | Pstr_attribute of attribute  (** [[\@\@\@id]] *)
  1006.   | Pstr_extension of extension * attributes  (** [[%%id]] *)

  1008. ‌and value_constraint =
  1009.   | Pvc_constraint of {
  1010.       locally_abstract_univars:string loc list;
  1011.       typ:core_type;
  1012.     }
  1013.   | Pvc_coercion of {ground:core_type option; coercion:core_type }
  1014.   (**
  1015.      - [Pvc_constraint { locally_abstract_univars=[]; typ}]
  1016.          is a simple type constraint on a value binding: [ let x : typ]
  1017.      - More generally, in [Pvc_constraint { locally_abstract_univars; typ}]
  1018.        [locally_abstract_univars] is the list of locally abstract type
  1019.        variables in [ let x: type a ... . typ ]
  1020.      - [Pvc_coercion { ground=None; coercion }] represents [let x :> typ]
  1021.      - [Pvc_coercion { ground=Some g; coercion }] represents [let x : g :> typ]
  1022.   *)

  1024. ‌and value_binding =
  1025.   {
  1026.     pvb_pat: pattern;
  1027.     pvb_expr: expression;
  1028.     pvb_constraint: value_constraint option;
  1029.     pvb_attributes: attributes;
  1030.     pvb_loc: Location.t;
  1031.   }(** [let pat : type_constraint = exp] *)

  1033. ‌and module_binding =
  1034.     {
  1035.      pmb_name: string option loc;
  1036.      pmb_expr: module_expr;
  1037.      pmb_attributes: attributes;
  1038.      pmb_loc: Location.t;
  1039.     }
  1040. (** Values of type [module_binding] represents [module X = ME] *)

  1042. (** {1 Toplevel} *)

  1044. (** {2 Toplevel phrases} *)

  1046. ‌type toplevel_phrase =
  1047.   | Ptop_def of structure
  1048.   | Ptop_dir of toplevel_directive  (** [#use], [#load] ... *)

  1050. ‌and toplevel_directive =
  1051.   {

  1053.     pdir_arg: directive_argument option;
  1054.     pdir_loc: Location.t;
  1055.   }

  1057. ‌and directive_argument =

  1060.     pdira_loc: Location.t;
  1061.   }

  1063. ‌and directive_argument_desc =
  1064.   | Pdir_string of string

  1066.   | Pdir_ident of Longident.t
  1067.   | Pdir_bool of bool
